on in dividends to its sole shareholder the government of québec its residential power rates are among the lowest in north america more than  percent of canada’s water resources are in québec and hydroquébec is the fourth largest hydropower producer in the world the company logo a stylized q fashioned out of a circle and a lightning bolt was designed by montrealbased design agency gagnonvalkus in  contents  history   beginnings and development   the second nationalisation   restructuring  present renewed growth  major outages  corporate structure and financial results  corporate structure  financial results  privatization debate  activities  power generation  transmission system  interconnections  investments  distribution  other activities  research and development  construction  international ventures  environment  effects on the natural environment  social effects and sustainable development  rates and customers  quebec market  residential customers  industrial customers  export markets  presidents  see also  footnotes  references  further reading  external links historyedit main article history of hydroquébec montreal light heat and power linemen  beginnings and developmentedit in quebec advocates for the creation of a public hydroelectric utility protested against high costs poor rural electrification and the lack of french speakers in management positions in hydroelectricity companies in  montreal light heat  power company was nationalised along with its subsidiary beauharnois power and hydroquébec was created to manage the companies quebec premier adélard godbout adopted a policy of investing  million dollars per year in rural electrification however in  the government changed and the new premier maurice duplessis was opposed to any form of government intervention in the economy local cooperatives were created to bring power to rural areas duplessis remained in power until  and during that time there were no further nationalisations of companies and hydroquébec mostly served the montreal area major projects included bersimis generating station completed in   mw bersimis generating station completed in   mw the beauharnois hydroelectric generating station completed in   mw carillon generating station built   mw between  and  hydroquébecs installed capacity increased from  to  mw while lowering residential power rates by half in the montreal area  the second nationalisationedit the spillway at the robertbourassa generating station can deal with a water flow twice as large as the saint lawrence river inaugurated in  the  mw generating station was at the heart of a network of  hydroelectric stations known as the james bay project duplessis conservative reign now known as the grande noirceur ended when he died in office in  the subsequent election of the quebec liberal party led by jean lesage marked the beginning of the quiet revolution a period of reform and modernisation the new government gave hydroquébec an exclusive mandate to develop new sites in  the government authorized it to acquire private electricity distributors including the gatineau power company and the shawinigan water  power company hydroquébec achieved provincewide scope all of the  rural coops accepted hydroquébec’s  buyout offer except saintjeanbaptistederouville which still exists major projects during this period included manicoutardes project a dam hydroelectric complex including the jeanlesage generating station  mw renélévesque generating station  mw and the danieljohnson dam  mw originally named manic manic and manic respectively because these stations were  kilometres away from the urban centers in southern quebec power was stepped up to  kv a world first led by engineer jeanjacques archambault churchill falls generating station  mw the station is in labrador and the government of quebec refused to allow power to be transferred through quebec forcing the negotiation of a contract where hydroquébec buys power from the project at  prices until the year  phase i of the james bay project hydroquébec worked with atomic energy of canada limited to build the candu reactor equipped gentilly nuclear generating station which closed in   restructuringedit because of the economic climate demand for electricity dropped significantly in the early s which led to structural changes at hydroquébec it became a joint stock company whose sole shareholder is québec government to which it pays an annual dividend it was also given the mandate to export power and to work in any energyrelated field in  the quebec – new england transmission began bringing power from the james bay project  kilometers south to the boston area phase ii of the james bay project started in  and took nine years to complete construction of the denisperron dam began in  present renewed growthedit in the late s the wholesale electricity market opened up across north america and hydroquébec opened its transmission system and wholesale electricity market to competition both inside and outside its tranditional service area the us federal energy regulatory commission granted hydroquébec a licence to sell wholesale electricity at market prices enabling hydroquébec to expand its market hydroquébec acquired a substantial share of noverco controller of natural gas distributor gaz métro to participate in that market in northeastern north america the rupert river diversion will channel part of the natural flow of the river orange on the map to the robertbourassa reservoir in  the agreement respecting a new relationship between the cree nation and the government of quebec between the grand council of the crees and the quebec government made possible the development of the eastmain reservoir the  million cad eastmaina and sarcelle powerhouses and rupert river diversion project this will provide water power to new turbines at eastmain or eastmaina and sarcelle powerhouses and will provide increased flow at the existing la grande generating station as well as robertbouras