olution a period of reform and modernisation the new government gave hydroquébec an exclusive mandate to develop new sites in  the government authorized it to acquire private electricity distributors including the gatineau power company and the shawinigan water  power company hydroquébec achieved provincewide scope all of the  rural coops accepted hydroquébec’s  buyout offer except saintjeanbaptistederouville which still exists major projects during this period included manicoutardes project a dam hydroelectric complex including the jeanlesage generating station  mw renélévesque generating station  mw and the danieljohnson dam  mw originally named manic manic and manic respectively because these stations were  kilometres away from the urban centers in southern quebec power was stepped up to  kv a world first led by engineer jeanjacques archambault churchill falls generating station  mw the station is in labrador and the government of quebec refused to allow power to be transferred through quebec forcing the negotiation of a contract where hydroquébec buys power from the project at  prices until the year  phase i of the james bay project hydroquébec worked with atomic energy of canada limited to build the candu reactor equipped gentilly nuclear generating station which closed in   restructuringedit because of the economic climate demand for electricity dropped significantly in the early s which led to structural changes at hydroquébec it became a joint stock company whose sole shareholder is québec government to which it pays an annual dividend it was also given the mandate to export power and to work in any energyrelated field in  the quebec – new england transmission began bringing power from the james bay project  kilometers south to the boston area phase ii of the james bay project started in  and took nine years to complete construction of the denisperron dam began in  present renewed growthedit in the late s the wholesale electricity market opened up across north america and hydroquébec opened its transmission system and wholesale electricity market to competition both inside and outside its tranditional service area the us federal energy regulatory commission granted hydroquébec a licence to sell wholesale electricity at market prices enabling hydroquébec to expand its market hydroquébec acquired a substantial share of noverco controller of natural gas distributor gaz métro to participate in that market in northeastern north america the rupert river diversion will channel part of the natural flow of the river orange on the map to the robertbourassa reservoir in  the agreement respecting a new relationship between the cree nation and the government of quebec between the grand council of the crees and the quebec government made possible the development of the eastmain reservoir the  million cad eastmaina and sarcelle powerhouses and rupert river diversion project this will provide water power to new turbines at eastmain or eastmaina and sarcelle powerhouses and will provide increased flow at the existing la grande generating station as well as robertbourassa or la grandea output will be  mw other stations commissioned since  are saintemarguerite in   mw péribonka in   mw rocherdegrandmère in   mw eastmain in   mw rapidedescœurs in   mw chuteallard in   mw mercier in   mw eastmaina in   mw la sarcelle in   mw romaine in   mw romaine in   mw romaine and romaine before  major outagesedit the north american ice storm of january  left  million hydroquébec customers in the dark for up to five weeks in  all of quebec and parts of new england and new brunswick lost power because of an equipment failure at a substation on the north shore the march  geomagnetic storm tripped circuit breakers on the transmission network causing a ninehour quebecwide blackout in the north american ice storm of  five days of freezing rain collapsed  kilometres  mi of high voltage power lines and over  kilometres  mi of medium and low voltage distribution lines in southern quebec up to  million customers were without power for up to five weeks corporate structure and financial resultsedit corporate structureedit hydroquébec generation and main transmission network as of  like its counterparts in the north american utility industry hydroquébec was reorganized in the late s to comply with electricity deregulation in the united states while still a vertically integrated company hydroquébec has created separate business units dealing with the generation transmission and distribution aspects of the business the transmission division transénergie was the first to be spun off in  in response to the us federal energy regulatory commissions publication of order  the restructuring was completed in the year  with the adoption of bill  which amended the act respecting the régie de lénergie to enact the functional separation of hydroquébecs various business units this functional separation and the creation of a socalled heritage pool french volume patrimonial of electricity echoed a recommendation of a merrill lynch study commissioned by the lucien bouchard government the january  report was aimed at finding a way to deregulate the electricity market in a way that was consistent with continental trends while maintaining the quebec social pact namely low uniform and stable rates across the province particularly in the residential sector legislation passed in  commits the generation division hydroquébec production to provide the distribution division hydroquébec distribution a yearly heritage pool of up to  twh of energy plus ancillary services—including an extra  twh for losses and a guaranteed peak capacity of  mw—at a set price of ¢ per kwh order in council  specifies quantities to be delivered for each of the  hourly intervals which vary from  to  mw hydroquébec distribution has to buy the remainder of the power and energy it needs—approximately  twh in  — by calling for tenders for longterm contracts open to all suppliers including hydroquébec production or targeted towards suppliers of a particular energy source like wind gas power biomass or small hydro for instance hydroquébec distribution launched calls for tenders in  and  for  and  mw of wind power respectively early deliveries started in  and the  wind farms under contract should be completely online by december  the transénergie and distribution divisions remain regulated by the régie de lénergie du québec quebec energy board an administrative tribunal established to set retail rates for electricity and natural gas for residential commercial and industrial service in the province based on a costofservice approach the régie also has extended powers including approval authority over every transmission and distributionrelated capital expenditure project exceeding c million approval of the terms of service and of longterm supply contracts dealing with customer complaints and the setting and enforcement of safety and reliability standards for the electric grid the generation division hydroquébec production is not subject to regulation by the régie however it must still submit every new construction project to a full environmental impact process including the release of extensive environmental studies the release of the studies are followed by a public hearing process conducted by the bureau daudiences publiques sur lenvironnement hydroquébec employed  people in  including  engineers making the company the largest employer of engineers in quebec v t e main subsidiaries of hydroquébec                           hydroquébec                                                                                                                                   société dénergie de la baie james        hydroquébec international  hydroquébec capitech  marketing dénergie hq        hydroquébec valtech                                                                  hq énergie        transénergie hq  gestion production hq        cedars rapids transmi